Files:
  screenshot-win32.{cpp|hpp}
  Provides easy to use functions for taking screenshots of the Windows desktop
  and saving them, using only the Windows API (GDI+).

  screenshot-simple.cpp
  Small example implementation with extra support for MSYS2 and Cygwin.
  If a filename is specified as the first argument on the commandline, then
  the image will be saved to that filename. Otherwise, the image will be
  saved as "screenshot.bmp" in the current working directory.

  screenshot-advanced.cpp
  Advanced implementation with extra command line options. Run
  "screenshot-advanced.exe -help" to get a full list of options.

License:
  screenshot-simple.cpp - unlicense (public domain)

  screenshot-win32.{cpp|hpp},
  screenshot-advanced.cpp - customized 3-Clause-BSD license

  Full license texts can be found at the file headers.

Compiling:
  Instructions to compile from command line can be found in the comment
  sections of screenshot-simple.cpp and screenshot-advanced.cpp.

